file.content:
# RFQ Page — Corrected Visual Design Spec
## Environment-aware. Mechanism-tagged. Full reskin.

---

## 1 · Scope

**Full visual reskin of the RFQ grid and its chrome to match the approved renderings in `RFQ Prototype.html`.**
Not a behavior list. Not four targeted features. Every surface.

---

## 2 · Environment constraints (read before touching anything)

| Constraint | What it means for this spec |
|---|---|
| AG Grid v35 Theming API (`themeQuartz.withParams`) is active via the shared theme service | All color/typography must go into `withParams({})`. CSS variables (`--ag-*`) and `.ag-theme-alpine` overrides do nothing here. |
| `::ng-deep` still works for structural CSS | Heights, borders, seam shadow, cell-class tints — all fine as `::ng-deep` in `rfq.component.scss`. |
| Column `pinned` defaults are overridden by saved Views | Changing `pinned: 'left'` in a colDef silently does nothing for any user with a saved View. Fix: update the "Default" View record in the DB, and optionally call `gridApi.applyColumnState(…, { applyOrder: false })` on `firstDataRendered` for identity columns only. |
| `flex` and `sizeColumnsToFit()` conflict | Pick one per grid. Sub-grid uses `flex: 1` on Note column — do **not** also call `sizeColumnsToFit()`. |
| Group-band row is currently `headerClass` on leaf columns, NOT a `ColGroupDef` | True collapsible groups require migrating to `ColGroupDef` + `columnGroupShow`. The tinting spec below covers both the old (headerClass on leaf) and the new (headerGroupClass on group) approach. |
| Role-based column visibility | `admin` sees all 24 pricing columns. `sales`/`designer` see only "Price for Sales" leaves. The scenario cell tints and group bands must look correct in both role sets. |
| Backend detail-grid col IDs | Live colIds in the factory-quote sub-grid are `price`, `name`, `note` (not `quote_price`, `vendor_note`). Spec uses live IDs. |

---

## 3 · Type system decision

**App-wide (RFQ + Item Detail in sync):**

| Usage | Family | Weights used |
|---|---|---|
| UI text, labels, header text, cell text | **Hanken Grotesk** | 400, 500, 600, 700 |
| Price codes, numeric figures, monospaced values | **IBM Plex Mono** | 400, 500, 600 |

Load via Google Fonts or self-host. Apply to the grid via the `fontFamily` theme param (Hanken Grotesk stack). Apply IBM Plex Mono to price-code cells via a cell renderer or `::ng-deep .ag-cell.cell-price-code { font-family: … }`.

---

## 4 · themeQuartz.withParams() — complete parameter table

Replace (or extend) the existing `themePink` in `grid-themes.config.ts` with these values.
**Use these exact param names.**

```typescript
export const themePink = themeQuartz.withParams({
  // ── Accent + selection ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  accentColor:                     '#D81B60',          // checkboxes, focus rings, range selection border
  rangeSelectionBackgroundColor:   'rgba(216,27,96,0.07)',
  rangeSelectionBorderColor:       '#D81B60',

  // ── Background + row colours ──────────────────────────────────────────
  backgroundColor:                 '#ffffff',
  oddRowBackgroundColor:           '#fbfcfd',          // subtle zebra (was none)
  rowHoverColor:                   '#fff5f8',          // faint pink hover
  selectedRowBackgroundColor:      '#fff5f8',          // matches hover; pink tint for selected row

  // ── Foreground / text ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  foregroundColor:                 '#1a202e',          // primary ink
  textColor:                       '#475569',          // secondary ink for cells

  // ── Borders ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  borderColor:                     '#e7e9ee',
  wrapperBorder:                   { color: '#e7e9ee', width: 1 },
  wrapperBorderRadius:             8,
  borderRadius:                    0,                  // no cell-level rounding
  rowBorder:                       { color: '#eef1f5', width: 1 },  // hairline row divider
  columnBorder:                    { color: '#e7e9ee', width: 1 },
  headerColumnBorder:              { color: '#e7e9ee', width: 1 },

  // ── Header ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  headerBackgroundColor:           '#f7f9fc',
  headerTextColor:                 '#475569',
  headerFontWeight:                600,
  headerFontSize:                  11,                 // pt; rendered uppercase via ::ng-deep below

  // ── Typography ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  fontFamily:
    '"Hanken Grotesk", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif',
  fontSize:                        13,                 // comfortable default; density overrides via setGridOption

  // ── Spacing ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  spacing:                         8,
  cellHorizontalPadding:           10,
  rowVerticalPaddingScale:         1,
});
```

> **Density switching** (`rowHeight`) is NOT a theme param; it goes through
> `this.gridApi.setGridOption('rowHeight', n)` + `this.gridApi.resetRowHeights()`.
> See §8 Toolbar for the density-toggle spec.

---

## 5 · Per-surface spec

Each item is tagged:
- **[theme param]** — value in `withParams({})` above, nothing else needed
- **[::ng-deep CSS]** — structural override in `rfq.component.scss`
- **[cell renderer]** — requires a custom Angular `ICellRendererAngularComp`
- **[colDef]** — property on the column definition in `rfq.grid.config.ts`
- **[component SCSS]** — styles in the component's own SCSS file

---

### 5a · 3-row header (group band · column header · floating filter)

The header has three stacked rows. Current heights: all 60px + filter 50px = 170px total.
Target: group band 36px + column header 48px + floating filter 44px = **128px total**.

```scss
// rfq.component.scss  — replaces the existing .ag-header-row block

// Row 1: scenario group band
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-row:first-child {
  height: 36px !important;
}

// Row 2: column headers (allows up to 2 lines of text)
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-row:nth-child(2) {
  height: 48px !important;
}

// Row 3: floating filters
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-row-floating-filter {
  height: 44px !important;
}

// Header text: uppercase + letter-spacing (font color/weight from theme param)
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-cell-text {
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  white-space: normal !important;
  line-height: 1.2;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2 !important;   // was 3; target shows 2 lines max
  max-height: 2.4em !important;
}
```
**[::ng-deep CSS]** for heights + text-transform.

#### Group-band row — per-family tints

Two families, two color systems. Replaces the current 8-color rainbow.

| Family | Band background | Band text / icon |
|---|---|---|
| **General** (Gen · FOB / POE / WHSE / MDDP) | `#dbe7fb` | `#2456b8` |
| **Licensed** (Lic · FOB / POE / WHSE / MDDP) | `#e9ddf7` | `#7a3bb8` |

When `ColGroupDef` is used (collapsible groups), set `headerGroupClass` on each group:
```typescript
// rfq.grid.config.ts — on each ColGroupDef
{ headerGroupClass: 'group-band-gen', … }  // General families
{ headerGroupClass: 'group-band-lic', … }  // Licensed families
```

CSS:
```scss
// rfq.component.scss — replaces the 8 group-header-* rules

// Group band cells (ColGroupDef header row)
::ng-deep .ag-header-group-cell.group-band-gen {
  background-color: #dbe7fb !important;
  color: #2456b8 !important;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}
::ng-deep .ag-header-group-cell.group-band-lic {
  background-color: #e9ddf7 !important;
  color: #7a3bb8 !important;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

// If still using headerClass on leaf columns (old approach, pre-ColGroupDef migration):
::ng-deep .ag-header-cell[class*="group-header-gen"] {
  background-color: #eaf1fd !important;
  .ag-header-cell-text, .ag-header-cell-label { color: #2456b8 !important; }
}
::ng-deep .ag-header-cell[class*="group-header-lic"] {
  background-color: #f3ecfb !important;
  .ag-header-cell-text, .ag-header-cell-label { color: #7a3bb8 !important; }
}
```
**[::ng-deep CSS]** + **[colDef `headerGroupClass`]**.

> The current 8-color system (blue/purple/green/orange/pink/teal/amber/lavender) is replaced
> by this 2-family system. Update the 8 `group-header-*` rules in the existing SCSS.

---

### 5b · Data rows

| Property | Value | Mechanism |
|---|---|---|
| Row background | `#ffffff` | [theme param] `backgroundColor` |
| Odd-row zebra | `#fbfcfd` | [theme param] `oddRowBackgroundColor` |
| Row hover | `#fff5f8` | [theme param] `rowHoverColor` |
| Selected row | `#fff5f8` | [theme param] `selectedRowBackgroundColor` |
| Row border (horizontal) | `1px solid #eef1f5` | [theme param] `rowBorder` |
| Cell border (vertical) | `1px solid #e7e9ee` | [theme param] `columnBorder` |
| Cell focus border | `1.5px solid #D81B60` | [::ng-deep CSS] `.ag-cell-focus` |
| Row-focus highlight | `rgba(216,27,96,0.06)` | [::ng-deep CSS] `.ag-row-focus` |
| Cell text | `#475569` 13px Hanken Grotesk | [theme param] `textColor`, `fontSize`, `fontFamily` |
| Numeric cells | `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums` | [::ng-deep CSS] `.ag-cell[col-id$="price"], [col-id$="margin"], …` or add `cellClass: 'cell-numeric'` to all numeric colDefs |
| Strong cells (Landed Cost, Price for Sales) | `#1a202e` font-weight 600 | [colDef `cellClass: 'cell-strong'`] + [::ng-deep] |

```scss
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell-focus {
  border: 1.5px solid #D81B60 !important;
}
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-row-focus {
  background-color: rgba(216, 27, 96, 0.06) !important;
}
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.cell-numeric {
  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  text-align: right;
}
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.cell-strong {
  color: #1a202e !important;
  font-weight: 600;
}
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.cell-price-code {
  font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace;
  font-size: 12px;
  color: #475569;
  font-weight: 500;
}
```

---

### 5c · Row group rows (RFQ Group band)

These are the `ag-full-width-row` cells that show the group name ("Spring Gift 2026" etc.).
Current: `#7f97a1` background — too dark and unmotivated.

```scss
// rfq.component.scss — replaces existing .ag-full-width-row rule
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-full-width-row,
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-row-group {
  background-color: #eef2f7 !important;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #d4dae3 !important;
}
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-row-group .ag-group-value,
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-row-group-leaf-indent {
  color: #1a202e !important;
  font-weight: 700 !important;
  font-size: 12px !important;
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
}
```
**[::ng-deep CSS]**

---

### 5d · Frozen identity pane — seam + active-row cross-pane highlight

The three identity columns (Price Code · Picture · Description) should be pinned left by default,
with a visible seam separating the pinned pane from the scrolling columns.

**Default pin state:**
Do NOT rely on `colDef.pinned = 'left'` alone — saved Views override it.
- Update the "Default" GridLayout record in the backend to include pinned state for
  `price_code`, `pic`, and `desc`.
- On `firstDataRendered` (after View is applied), call:
  ```typescript
  this.gridApi.applyColumnState({
    state: [
      { colId: 'price_code', pinned: 'left' },
      { colId: 'pic',        pinned: 'left' },
      { colId: 'desc',       pinned: 'left' },
    ],
    defaultState: { pinned: null }   // leave all others as the view says
  });
  ```
  Note: pass `applyOrder: false` so you don't reorder columns.

**Seam CSS:**
```scss
// rfq.component.scss

// Header seam — last pinned header cell
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-pinned-left-header .ag-header-cell:last-child,
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-cell.ag-cell-last-left-pinned {
  border-right: 1.5px solid #d4dae3 !important;
  box-shadow: 4px 0 8px -4px rgba(20, 30, 50, 0.18);
}

// Cell seam — last pinned data cell in each row
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.ag-cell-last-left-pinned {
  border-right: 1.5px solid #d4dae3 !important;
  box-shadow: 4px 0 8px -4px rgba(20, 30, 50, 0.18);
}

// Active-row highlight crosses the seam: pinned cells must also show the bg
// (AG Grid's selectedRowBackgroundColor already propagates; this reinforces it)
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-row-selected .ag-cell {
  background-color: transparent !important;  // let row bg show through
}
```
**[::ng-deep CSS]** + **[TypeScript: `applyColumnState` on `firstDataRendered`]**

---

### 5e · Scenario pricing cells — body tints + Price for Sales emphasis

Add `cellClass` to the 24 scenario leaf columns in `rfq.grid.config.ts`:

```typescript
// All Gen columns  → cellClass: 'scenario-gen'
// All Lic columns  → cellClass: 'scenario-lic'
// Price for Sales leaves only → cellClass: 'scenario-gen scenario-gen--sales' etc.

addColumn("Gen FOB Price for Sales", "gen_fob_price_sales", 130, {
  headerClass: "group-header-gen-fob",
  cellClass: 'scenario-gen scenario-gen--sales',
  roles: ['admin', 'sales', 'designer']
}),
addColumn("Gen FOB Sell Price", "gen_fob_sell_price", 130, {
  headerClass: "group-header-gen-fob",
  cellClass: 'scenario-gen',
  roles: ['admin']
}),
// … repeat for all 24 columns
```

CSS:
```scss
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.scenario-gen {
  background-color: #eaf1fd;
}
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.scenario-lic {
  background-color: #f3ecfb;
}
// Price for Sales — always-visible leaf, bolder
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.scenario-gen--sales {
  background-color: #e0ecfd !important;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #1a202e !important;
  font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  text-align: right;
}
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.scenario-lic--sales {
  background-color: #ead9f7 !important;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #1a202e !important;
  font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  text-align: right;
}
// Margin cell — conditional color via cellClassRules
// Add to colDef: cellClassRules: { 'margin-good': p => p.value >= 45, 'margin-warn': p => p.value < 35 }
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.margin-good { color: #1f9d6b !important; }
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-cell.margin-warn { color: #c98a08 !important; }
```
**[colDef `cellClass` / `cellClassRules`]** + **[::ng-deep CSS]**

---

### 5f · Status cell — colored pill

**[needs cell renderer]** `StatusPillCellRenderer`

The cell currently shows plain text. Replace with a chip component.

Markup (inline template or component):
```html
<span class="status-pill status-pill--{{value | lowercase}}">
  <span class="status-pill__dot"></span>
  {{ value }}
</span>
```

Styles (in the renderer's `styles` or via `::ng-deep`):
```scss
.status-pill {
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px;
  padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 20px;
  font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4;
  &__dot { width: 5px; height: 5px; border-radius: 50%; }
  &--active  { background: #e8f6ef; color: #1f9d6b; .status-pill__dot { background: #1f9d6b; } }
  &--draft   { background: #fbf2dd; color: #c98a08; .status-pill__dot { background: #c98a08; } }
  &--inactive{ background: #eef1f5; color: #7b8a9a; .status-pill__dot { background: #7b8a9a; } }
}
```
Register as `cellRenderer: 'statusPillRenderer'` in the `status` colDef.

---

### 5g · Step cell — dot + text indicator

**[needs cell renderer]** `StepIndicatorCellRenderer`

No background chip — just a colored dot + label text. Subtler than the Status pill.

```html
<span class="step-indicator">
  <span class="step-indicator__dot" [style.background]="dotColor"></span>
  {{ shortLabel }}
</span>
```

Step → dot color mapping:
| Step value | Short label | Dot color |
|---|---|---|
| `@sales for details` | Sales detail | `#6366f1` |
| `@sourcing` | Sourcing | `#0ea5e9` |
| `@factories` | Factories | `#f59e0b` |
| `px sent to sales` | Px → Sales | `#10b981` |
| `px sent to cust` | Px → Customer | `#22c55e` |
| _(anything else)_ | _(as-is)_ | `#7b8a9a` |

```scss
.step-indicator {
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
  font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; color: #475569;
  &__dot { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; flex: none; }
}
```
Register as `cellRenderer: 'stepIndicatorRenderer'` in the `step` colDef.

---

### 5h · Re-quote / price-requested cell

Currently `.price-requested-cell { background: #ffe082 }`. Update to match tokens:

```scss
// rfq.component.scss — update existing rule
::ng-deep .price-requested-cell {
  background-color: #fdeede !important;  // was #ffe082
  color: #e8833a !important;
}
```
**[::ng-deep CSS]** — no new renderer needed.

---

### 5i · Toolbar

The existing `.rfq-toolbar`, `.create-btn`, `.secondary-btn` classes are kept.
Update values only:

```scss
// rfq.component.scss

// Primary button — radius up from 4px → 8px, shadow refine
.create-btn {
  background-color: #D81B60 !important;
  border-radius: 8px !important;           // was 4px
  height: 36px !important;                 // was 40px (tighter)
  box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(216,27,96,0.3) !important;
  font-weight: 600 !important;
}

// Secondary ghost buttons — softer border, matching radius
.secondary-btn {
  border: 1px solid #e7e9ee !important;   // was #cfd8dc
  border-radius: 8px !important;          // was 4px
  height: 36px !important;               // was 40px
  color: #475569 !important;
  mat-icon { color: #7b8a9a !important; }
}

// Hairline dividers between toolbar groups
.toolbar-divider {
  width: 1px; height: 22px;
  background: #e7e9ee;
  align-self: center;
}
```

Add `.toolbar-divider` elements in `rfq.component.html` between `toolbar-left` and the filter group, and between the filter group and view group.

**Density segmented toggle** (new UI element in the toolbar right, before the utilities):
```html
<!-- rfq.component.html, inside toolbar-right → view-group -->
<div class="density-toggle">
  <button [class.active]="density === 'compact'"    (click)="setDensity('compact')">Compact</button>
  <button [class.active]="density === 'standard'"   (click)="setDensity('standard')">Standard</button>
  <button [class.active]="density === 'comfortable'"(click)="setDensity('comfortable')">Comfortable</button>
</div>
```
```scss
.density-toggle {
  display: inline-flex; background: #eef1f5; border-radius: 8px; padding: 2px; gap: 2px;
  button {
    height: 28px; padding: 0 11px; border-radius: 6px; border: none; cursor: pointer;
    background: transparent; color: #7b8a9a; font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 500;
    font-family: inherit; transition: background .1s, color .1s;
    &.active {
      background: #fff; color: #1a202e; font-weight: 600;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    }
  }
}
```

Density grid options (TypeScript in `rfq.component.ts`):
```typescript
density: 'compact' | 'standard' | 'comfortable' = 'standard';

readonly DENSITY_MAP = {
  compact:     { rowHeight: 30 },
  standard:    { rowHeight: 36 },
  comfortable: { rowHeight: 44 },
} as const;

setDensity(d: typeof this.density) {
  this.density = d;
  this.gridApi.setGridOption('rowHeight', this.DENSITY_MAP[d].rowHeight);
  this.gridApi.resetRowHeights();
  localStorage.setItem('rfq:density', d);
}
ngOnInit() {
  this.density = (localStorage.getItem('rfq:density') as any) ?? 'standard';
}
// Apply initial density once gridApi is ready (in gridReady callback):
this.gridApi.setGridOption('rowHeight', this.DENSITY_MAP[this.density].rowHeight);
```

**[component SCSS `.density-toggle`]** + **[TypeScript `setDensity()`]**

---

### 5j · Status bar

The custom status bar component (`custom-status-bar.component`) already exists.
Update its SCSS to match tokens.

```scss
// custom-status-bar.component.scss
:host {
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px;
  padding: 0 20px; height: 40px;
  font-family: 'Hanken Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif;
  font-size: 12.5px; color: #475569;
  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  background: #fff; border-top: 1px solid #e7e9ee;
}
.stat-divider {
  width: 1px; height: 14px; background: #e7e9ee; flex: none;
}
.stat-label { color: #7b8a9a; }
.stat-value { color: #1a202e; font-weight: 600; }
// Pager buttons
.pager-btn {
  width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 7px;
  border: 1px solid #e7e9ee; background: #fff; color: #475569;
  display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px;
  &:disabled { opacity: 0.4; cursor: default; }
}
// Page-size selector
.page-size-select {
  height: 28px; padding: 0 8px 0 10px; border-radius: 7px;
  border: 1px solid #e7e9ee; background: #fff;
  font-size: 12.5px; color: #1a202e; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer;
}
```
**[component SCSS]** for the status bar component.

---

### 5k · Factory-quote sub-grid (detail-cell-renderer)

The container card:
```scss
// detail-cell-renderer.component.scss
:host {
  display: block;
  background: #eef3f9;
  border-left: 3px solid #D81B60;
  padding: 14px 16px 16px;
}
.subgrid-header {
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;
  .title { font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 700; color: #1a202e; }
  .count-badge {
    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: #7b8a9a;
    background: #fff; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1px 8px;
  }
  .summary { font-size: 11.5px; color: #7b8a9a; }
}
```

**Column order and flex policy** in `rfq.detail.grid.config.ts`
(use live colIds `price`, `name`, `note`):

```typescript
// Ordered: Name · Price · Lead · CBM · Price Terms · FOB Country · FOB Port · Note (flex)
addColumn("Name",            "name",         220, { pinned: 'left', minWidth: 180, sortable: true }),
addColumn("Price",           "price",        120, { minWidth: 100,  sortable: true, type: 'rightAligned' }),
addColumn("Lead Time (days)","lead_time",    110, { minWidth: 90,   sortable: true, type: 'rightAligned' }),
addColumn("CBM/pc",          "cbm_pc",       110, { minWidth: 90,   sortable: true, type: 'rightAligned' }),
addColumn("Price Terms",     "price_terms",  120, { minWidth: 100,  sortable: true }),
addColumn("FOB Country",     "fob_country",  120, { minWidth: 100,  sortable: true }),
addColumn("FOB Port",        "fob_port",     120, { minWidth: 100,  sortable: true }),
addColumn("Note",            "note",  undefined,  { flex: 1, minWidth: 200, sortable: false }),
// Do NOT call sizeColumnsToFit() — flex handles it.
```

The detail sub-grid must have its own theme. Apply the same `themePink` (or a variant with
`backgroundColor: '#eef3f9'`) via `[theme]` input on the detail grid's `ag-grid-angular`.

**Row styling** (applied via `getRowClass` in the detail grid options):
```scss
// Applied to detail grid rows via cellClassRules + ::ng-deep on detail renderer
